items.title: Six West Africans deported from US sent to Togo despite legal fight
items.description: They had started legal action against Ghana for agreeing to accept them from the US.

items.title: Moment sinkhole pulls down power lines in busy Bangkok street
items.description: Social media footage showed the massive crater in Thailand's capital leaving cars teetering on the edge.

items.title: Howling winds and sheets of rain: In the eye of a typhoon in China
items.description: The strong winds hit in waves - and standing upright is almost impossible, our correspondent writes.

items.title: Jimmy Kimmel calls out 'anti-American' threats to free speech in tearful TV return
items.description: The comedian returned from a brief suspension after comments he made about the killing of conservative activist Charlie Kirk.

items.title: Kyiv can win all of Ukraine back from Russia, Trump says
items.description: The US president says Ukraine can win back land with support from Nato and Europe, marking a major shift in his position.
